---
title: Slammin' Lemon Salmon with Warm Butter Bean and Zucchini Salad
description: One thing that always puts a smile on our face after a long day is a plate full of bright and cheery veggies and a gorgeous piece of salmon—just looking at all that deliciousness is a form of food therapy in itself. Of course, it helps if the flavors are just as lively. Which they are in this recipe: the bean and veggie salad gets an aromatic boost from mustard and coriander, while the salmon is bathed in a sunshine-y mix of lemon and butter.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w14-r4-28676b05.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w14-r4-5f79e8bc.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 54 g
  fiber: 23 g
  sodium: 530 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/w14-r4-58a62f54043c3c0bf934a4f3
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Drain and rinse @butter beans{1%box}. Finely dice @red onion{1}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Chop @zucchini{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Add @sugar snap peas{4%ounce} and zucchini. Cook until snap peas are tender but still crisp and zucchini has softened, about ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat another large drizzle of olive oil in same pan. Season @skin-on salmon{12%ounce} all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in pan skinside down. Cook until almost opaque in center, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Add @butter{1%tbsp} to pan and juice of half the lemon. Spoon butter and lemon over salmon continuously until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove salmon from pan and set aside.

Lower heat under pan to medium and add garlic. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} and @ground coriander{1%tsp} and cook, stirring, another ~{30%seconds}. Add butter beans and veggie mixture. Cook, tossing, until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} to pan. Simmer until slightly reduced, about ~{3%minutes}. Stir in half the cilantro.

Divide veggie and bean mixture between plates, then top with salmon. Squeeze lemon over plates and sprinkle with remaining cilantro.